{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2595d67c-67db-4776-ad18-9803923eeab4","content":"I don't see the project on disk, but here's how to configure it. Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout (the standard for local MCP servers).\n- **`command` / `args`** — Uses `dotnet run` to build and launch your project.\n- Your server must read JSON-RPC messages from stdin and write responses to stdout. Make sure you don't write logs/debug output to stdout (use stderr instead).\n\nIf you publish a self-contained executable instead, replace with:\n```json\n\"command\": \"src/MyMcpServer/bin/Release/net8.0/MyMcpServer\"\n```\n\nAfter saving, restart VS Code or run **\"MCP: List Servers\"** from the command palette to verify it connects.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"414a553d-2c0e-4f09-af4e-a9bb7542b378","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist yet, but the user said they built it. They're just asking how to configure mcp.json. I can provide the configuration guidance directly.","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"3C07:20979:1FF6185:23DBE35:69E81CDC"},"id":"d53d5170-aef4-460d-a672-2d02737b8cb1","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:57:09.230Z","parentId":"4fe2d3b5-d4e2-4ea2-962a-7f853c6efaa3"}
